Gonna test this out right quick! Just a quick note - since this isn't a plugin, you're not obligated to package the source files with it, still nice though!

It took me a bit of effort to get this thing into space without damaging its payload. I started calling the upper stage fairings "death flowers" since they kept tearing solar panels and antennae off of my service module (my own build, not the included module). I had to use PDCWolf Perfectrons to kick those fairings clear of the cargo. I upped the first stage thrust 20% and the upper stage thrust 25% (no changes to Isp), and I can easily get an Apollo-like mission (service module and lander) to the Mun without using any of their fuel until I fine-tune my approach. I also used MechJeb to limit acceleration to 25 m/s^2, which helped a lot with the bucking and twisting because of the CoM / CoT distance before the first stage separation.

The excessive thrust and fuel is to "KSP part" scale with the real thing. If someone wants to rebalance it, go right ahead.

Okay, even 20% and 25% doesn't cut it. It's either 33% or bust.

- EditÃ‚Â²:

I've spent at least five hours devising a workable ascent profile (sucks to have lost the old data).

As the S-IVB lacks a fair bit of punch, you will need some time to get your speed up. Hence anything around 100 km usually ends in embarassing suborbital trajectories due to mere lack of time.

My last initial orbit was 150 Km with the following Mechjeb settings:

Turn start: 2 Km

Turn end: 100 Km

Final flight path angle: 10Ã‚Â°

Profile: 60%

Nothing broke apart during ascent and the panels separated without touching anything. Also, despite some slight wobbling, there was no need for extra control surfaces*.

Other profiles are welcome though.

Hint:

Get the ullage rockets from NovaPunch and attach them to the S-IVB. Then put a camera next to the engine and watch the staging.

(Something akin to this: http://i1188.photobucket.com/albums/z416/DArkB0mb3rz22/apollo-4-staging.gif)

Also, NP provides a LES and a stackable parachute. Put a docking port between the parachute and the LES, make sure to assign LES functions correctly et voilÃƒÂ , Kerpollo 7. Don't forget to take aspirine and handkerchiefs with you though.
